turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why did he invite her?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why does that bother you?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's been three years.  Why all of a sudden?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well maybe- maybe he just wanted to see her again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Nobody comes seven hundred miles just to see.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What do you mean?  He was brought up next door to the girl his whole life.  Why shouldn't he want to see her again?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Don't look at me like that.  He didn't tell me anymore than he told you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's not going to marry him.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How do you know he's even thinking about it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's got that about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well so what.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What's going on here, Joe?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Listen kid.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, line.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Uh, Then why is she still-she's not his girl, Joe

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's not his girl, Joe.  She knows she's not.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can't read her mind.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Then why is she still single?  New York is full of men.  Why hasn't she married?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Probably a hundred people told her she's foolish but she's waited.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How do you know why she waited?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because she knows what I know that's why.  She's faithful as a rock.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: In my worst moments, I think of her waiting and I know again that I'm right.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Look it's a nice day.  What are we arguing for?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Nobody in this house dares take her faith away, Joe.  Strangers might but not his father, not his brother.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What do you want me to do?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I want you to act like he's coming back, both of you.  Don't think I haven't noticed you since he invited her.  I won't stand for any nonsense.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: But Kate-

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because if he's not coming back, I'll kill myself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Laugh, laugh at me, but why did that happen the very night she came back?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She goes to sleep in his room and his memorial breaks in pieces.  Look, look at it.  Joe-

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Believe with me, Joe.  I can't stand alone.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just last week a man showed up in Detroit missing longer than Larry.  You read it yourself.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Alright.  Alright.  Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You above all have got to believe.  You.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why me above all?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just don't stop believing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What does that mean, me above all?  Look at you.  You're shaking.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I can't help it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What have I got to hide?  What the hell is matter with you Kate?
